Theory. 

Explanation: This paper belongs to the sub-category of AI theory as it deals with the theoretical analysis of repeated stage games with bounded players. The paper does not involve the application of any specific AI technique such as case-based reasoning, genetic algorithms, neural networks, probabilistic methods, reinforcement learning, or rule learning. Instead, it focuses on developing a theoretical framework to handle the problem of optimality and domination in such games.
